{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":95,"text":"I'm really excited to be here today."},{"time":1898,"text":"I'll show you some stuff\nthat's just ready to come out of the lab,"},{"time":5024,"text":"literally, and I'm really glad\nthat you guys"},{"time":7824,"text":"are going to be among\nthe first to see it in person,"},{"time":10320,"text":"because I really think this is going\nto really change"},{"time":12833,"text":"the way we interact\nwith machines from this point on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15339,"text":"Now, this is a rear-projected\ndrafting table."},{"time":18038,"text":"It's about 36 inches wide"},{"time":19284,"text":"and it's equipped\nwith a multi-touch sensor."},{"time":21391,"text":"Normal touch sensors that you see,"},{"time":23059,"text":"like on a kiosk\nor interactive whiteboards,"},{"time":25220,"text":"can only register one point\nof contact at a time."},{"time":28137,"text":"This thing allows you to have\nmultiple points at the same time."},{"time":31876,"text":"They can use both my hands;\nI can use chording actions;"},{"time":35214,"text":"I can just go right up and use\nall 10 fingers if I wanted to."},{"time":38597,"text":"You know, like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39778,"text":"Now, multi-touch sensing\nisn't completely new."},{"time":44345,"text":"People like Bill Buxton have been\nplaying around with it in the '80s."},{"time":47622,"text":"However, the approach I built here\nis actually high-resolution,"},{"time":51674,"text":"low-cost, and probably\nmost importantly, very scalable."},{"time":55000,"text":"So, the technology, you know,"},{"time":57361,"text":"isn't the most exciting thing\nhere right now,"},{"time":59831,"text":"other than probably\nits newfound accessibility."},{"time":62173,"text":"What's really interesting here\nis what you can do with it"},{"time":65722,"text":"and the kind of interfaces\nyou can build on top of it."},{"time":69141,"text":"So let's see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71111,"text":"So, for instance, we have\na lava lamp application here."},{"time":75448,"text":"Now, you can see,"},{"time":77174,"text":"I can use both of my hands to kind\nof squeeze and put the blobs together."},{"time":80627,"text":"I can inject heat into the system here,"},{"time":83194,"text":"or I can pull it apart\nwith two of my fingers."},{"time":85400,"text":"It's completely intuitive;\nthere's no instruction manual."},{"time":88154,"text":"The interface just kind of disappears."},{"time":90000,"text":"This started out as a screensaver app"},{"time":91944,"text":"that one of the Ph.D. students\nin our lab, Ilya Rosenberg, made."},{"time":95015,"text":"But I think its true identity\ncomes out here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100153,"text":"Now what's great about a multi-touch\nsensor is that, you know,"},{"time":103100,"text":"I could be doing this\nwith as many fingers here,"},{"time":105861,"text":"but of course multi-touch\nalso inherently means multi-user."},{"time":108863,"text":"Chris could be interacting\nwith another part of Lava,"},{"time":111386,"text":"while I play around with it here."},{"time":113044,"text":"You can imagine\na new kind of sculpting tool,"},{"time":115164,"text":"where I'm kind of warming something up,\nmaking it malleable,"},{"time":118167,"text":"and then letting it cool down\nand solidifying in a certain state."},{"time":125712,"text":"Google should have\nsomething like this in their lobby."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128683,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"I'll show you a little more\nof a concrete example here,"},{"time":137296,"text":"as this thing loads."},{"time":139181,"text":"This is a photographer's\nlight-box application."},{"time":141922,"text":"Again, I can use both of my hands\nto interact and move photos around."},{"time":145923,"text":"But what's even cooler\nis that if I have two fingers,"},{"time":149502,"text":"I can actually grab a photo and then\nstretch it out like that really easily."},{"time":153656,"text":"I can pan, zoom\nand rotate it effortlessly."},{"time":157146,"text":"I can do that grossly\nwith both of my hands,"},{"time":159501,"text":"or I can do it just with two fingers\non each of my hands together."},{"time":162729,"text":"If I grab the canvas, I can do\nthe same thing -- stretch it out."},{"time":165780,"text":"I can do it simultaneously,\nholding this down,"},{"time":167963,"text":"and gripping on another one,\nstretching this out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170286,"text":"Again, the interface just disappears here."},{"time":172538,"text":"There's no manual."},{"time":173595,"text":"This is exactly what you expect,"},{"time":175921,"text":"especially if you haven't interacted\nwith a computer before."},{"time":179000,"text":"Now, when you have initiatives\nlike the $100 laptop,"},{"time":181728,"text":"I kind of cringe at the idea"},{"time":183285,"text":"of introducing a whole new\ngeneration to computing"},{"time":185886,"text":"with this standard\nmouse-and-windows-pointer interface."},{"time":188648,"text":"This is something that I think\nis really the way"},{"time":191808,"text":"we should be interacting\nwith machines from now on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194473,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"Now, of course, I can bring up a keyboard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203024,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":208000,"text":"And I can bring that around,\nput that up there."},{"time":211213,"text":"Obviously, this is a standard keyboard,"},{"time":213095,"text":"but of course I can rescale it\nto make it work well for my hands."},{"time":216201,"text":"That's really important, because\nthere's no reason in this day and age"},{"time":219558,"text":"that we should be conforming\nto a physical device."},{"time":221922,"text":"That leads to bad things, like RSI."},{"time":223693,"text":"We have so much technology nowadays"},{"time":226494,"text":"that these interfaces\nshould start conforming to us."},{"time":230547,"text":"There's so little applied now\nto actually improving"},{"time":234548,"text":"the way we interact with interfaces\nfrom this point on."},{"time":237151,"text":"This keyboard is probably actually\nthe really wrong direction to go."},{"time":240366,"text":"You can imagine, in the future,\nas we develop this kind of technology,"},{"time":243692,"text":"a keyboard that kind of automatically\ndrifts as your hand moves away,"},{"time":247119,"text":"and really intelligently anticipates\nwhich key you're trying to stroke."},{"time":251477,"text":"So -- again, isn't this great?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255051,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257047,"text":"Audience: Where's your lab?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258834,"text":"Jeff Han: I'm a research scientist\nat NYU in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265341,"text":"Here's an example of another kind of app.\nI can make these little fuzz balls."},{"time":269000,"text":"It'll remember the strokes I'm making."},{"time":271358,"text":"Of course I can do it with all my hands."},{"time":273301,"text":"It's pressure-sensitive."},{"time":275905,"text":"What's neat about that is,"},{"time":277485,"text":"I showed that two-finger gesture\nthat zooms in really quickly."},{"time":280474,"text":"Because you don't have\nto switch to a hand tool"},{"time":282705,"text":"or the magnifying glass tool,"},{"time":284135,"text":"you can just continuously make things"},{"time":286698,"text":"in real multiple scales,\nall at the same time."},{"time":289076,"text":"I can create big things out here,"},{"time":291113,"text":"but I can go back\nand really quickly go back"},{"time":293235,"text":"to where I started,\nand make even smaller things here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297271,"text":"This is going to be really important"},{"time":299182,"text":"as we start getting to things\nlike data visualization."},{"time":302239,"text":"For instance, I think\nwe all enjoyed Hans Rosling's talk,"},{"time":304930,"text":"and he really emphasized the fact\nI've been thinking about for a long time:"},{"time":308480,"text":"We have all this great data,"},{"time":309855,"text":"but for some reason,\nit's just sitting there."},{"time":311976,"text":"We're not accessing it."},{"time":313119,"text":"And one of the reasons why I think that is"},{"time":316666,"text":"will be helped by things like graphics\nand visualization and inference tools,"},{"time":321406,"text":"but I also think a big part of it"},{"time":323291,"text":"is going to be having better interfaces,"},{"time":325371,"text":"to be able to drill down\ninto this kind of data,"},{"time":327635,"text":"while still thinking\nabout the big picture here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330460,"text":"Let me show you another app here.\nThis is called WorldWind."},{"time":333463,"text":"It's done by NASA."},{"time":334626,"text":"We've all seen Google Earth;"},{"time":337480,"text":"this is an open-source version of that."},{"time":339462,"text":"There are plug-ins to be able\nto load in different data sets"},{"time":343010,"text":"that NASA's collected over the years."},{"time":344833,"text":"As you can see, I can use\nthe same two-fingered gestures"},{"time":347477,"text":"to go down and go in really seamlessly."},{"time":349983,"text":"There's no interface, again."},{"time":351387,"text":"It really allows anybody\nto kind of go in --"},{"time":354682,"text":"and it just does\nwhat you'd expect, you know?"},{"time":357669,"text":"Again, there's just no interface here.\nThe interface just disappears."},{"time":363000,"text":"I can switch to different data views."},{"time":364900,"text":"That's what's neat about this app here."},{"time":367118,"text":"NASA's really cool."},{"time":368299,"text":"These hyper-spectral images\nare false-colored so you can --"},{"time":371085,"text":"it's really good for determining\nvegetative use."},{"time":375887,"text":"Well, let's go back to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380312,"text":"The great thing\nabout mapping applications --"},{"time":382510,"text":"it's not really 2D, it's 3D."},{"time":384024,"text":"So, again, with a multi-point interface,\nyou can do a gesture like this --"},{"time":387540,"text":"so you can be able\nto tilt around like that --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391001,"text":"(Surprised laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":392899,"text":"It's not just simply relegated\nto a kind of 2D panning and motion."},{"time":396105,"text":"This gesture is just putting\ntwo fingers down --"},{"time":398764,"text":"it's defining an axis of tilt --\nand I can tilt up and down that way."},{"time":402441,"text":"We just came up with that on the spot,"},{"time":404543,"text":"it's probably not the right thing to do,"},{"time":406504,"text":"but there's such interesting things\nyou can do with this interface."},{"time":411000,"text":"It's just so much fun\nplaying around with it, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413958,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415335,"text":"And so the last thing\nI want to show you is --"},{"time":418000,"text":"I'm sure we can all think\nof a lot of entertainment apps"},{"time":420701,"text":"that you can do with this thing."},{"time":422249,"text":"I'm more interested in the creative\napplications we can do with this."},{"time":426323,"text":"Now, here's a simple application here --\nI can draw out a curve."},{"time":431201,"text":"And when I close it,\nit becomes a character."},{"time":434785,"text":"But the neat thing about it\nis I can add control points."},{"time":437786,"text":"And then what I can do is manipulate them\nwith both of my fingers at the same time."},{"time":441787,"text":"And you notice what it does."},{"time":444253,"text":"It's kind of a puppeteering thing,"},{"time":446832,"text":"where I can use as many fingers\nas I have to draw and make --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458274,"text":"Now, there's a lot of actual math\ngoing on under here"},{"time":461000,"text":"for this to control this mesh\nand do the right thing."},{"time":466183,"text":"This technique of being able to manipulate\na mesh here, with multiple control points,"},{"time":471899,"text":"is actually state of the art."},{"time":473399,"text":"It was released at SIGGRAPH last year."},{"time":475247,"text":"It's a great example\nof the kind of research I really love:"},{"time":478041,"text":"all this compute power\nto make things do the right things,"},{"time":480864,"text":"intuitive things,\nto do exactly what you expect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"So, multi-touch interaction research\nis a very active field right now in HCI."},{"time":492000,"text":"I'm not the only one doing it,\na lot of other people are getting into it."},{"time":495500,"text":"This kind of technology is going to let\neven more people get into it,"},{"time":498769,"text":"I'm looking forward to interacting\nwith all of you over the next few days"},{"time":502285,"text":"and seeing how it can apply\nto your respective fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504846,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506028,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}